RoadRescue360 ‚Äì Real-Time Breakdown Assistance Platform:

RoadRescue360 is a full-stack, real-time web platform designed to assist drivers during vehicle breakdowns. The system enables users to report vehicle issues, track nearby technicians live, and continue their journey through replacement vehicles or alternative transport options.

This project demonstrates real-time systems, scalable backend architecture, secure authentication, geolocation services, and role-based access control, simulating a real-world production-grade application.

Project Motivation

Vehicle breakdowns often occur unexpectedly and require fast, reliable assistance. RoadRescue360 aims to:

Reduce response time during breakdowns

Improve coordination between customers and service providers

Provide transparency through live tracking

Ensure seamless journey continuation

Key Features
Breakdown Booking

Issue-based breakdown reporting:

Engine failure

Battery issue

Tyre puncture

Fuel shortage

Accident

User-friendly booking flow with issue description and location sharing

Real-Time GPS Tracking

Live tracking of:

Customers

Mechanics

Tow trucks

Implemented using WebSockets (Socket.io)

Integrated with Google Maps API for live map visualization

Intelligent Service Assignment

Automatically assigns the nearest available technician or towing service

Uses geospatial distance calculations

Priority-based dispatch system

Journey Continuation

Car replacement option

Rental car / taxi service integration (mock APIs)

Seamless transition after breakdown resolution

Secure Authentication & Authorization

JWT-based authentication

Role-based access control:

User

Technician

Admin

Admin Dashboard

View and manage all service requests

Monitor technician availability

Configure pricing

Analytics and system insights

